{"add":{"doc":{"id":"aea13916f73acbe92d61b7e52544390be542509a2174eccb9c35571c8a4b6ba7","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Broadcasting_House_by_Stephen_Craven.jpg/150px-Broadcasting_House_by_Stephen_Craven.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Broadcasting House in Portland Place, London, is the official headquarters of the BBC. It is home to six of the ten BBC national radio networks, BBC Radio 1, BBC Radio 1xtra, BBC Asian Network, BBC Radio 3, BBC Radio 4, and BBC Radio 4 Extra. It is also the home of BBC News, which relocated to the building from BBC Television Centre in 2013. On the front of the building are statues of Prospero and Ariel, characters from William Shakespeare's play The Tempest, sculpted by Eric Gill. Renovation of Broadcasting House began in 2002 and was completed in 2013."]}}}